%F A063984 a(n) = A070911(n)/2 - n/2 + 1. [Simpson]
%F A063984 See Barany & Tokushige for asymptotics.
%F A063984 a(n) = min(g: A322345(g) >= n). - _Andrey Zabolotskiy_, Apr 23 2023
%e A063984 For example, every convex pentagon whose vertices are lattice points contains at least one lattice point and it is not difficult to construct such a pentagon with only one interior lattice point. Thus a(5) = 1.
